[31.483589, "o", "/app/environment/docs/emit_contract.md:3:Operators treat the emitted JSON as the authoritative audit for one manifest run. Row digests cover per-unit pipe serializations; the top digest covers the header line plus each row serialization in manifest unit order.\r\n/app/environment/docs/emit_contract.md:5:The instruction at `/app/instruction.md` states the tested field formulas and digest packing rules used by verifiers.\r\n/app/environment/docs/overview.md:3:The CMake tree under `/app/environment` builds `forge_emit`, an offline lane audit tool that reads a release manifest and companion unit record files, then emits JSON at `/app/output/forge_emit.json` while persisting resume checkpoints at `/app/output/forge_checkpoint.json`.\r\n/app/environment/docs/overview.md:7:See `/app/environment/docs/emit_contract.md` for operator notes and `/app/environment/docs/persistence_notes.md` for checkpoint behavior.\r\n/app/environment/docs/persistence_notes.md:1:# Lane checkpoint persistence\r\n/app/environment/docs/persistence_note"]
[31.483609, "o", "s.md:3:The runner maintains `/app/output/forge_checkpoint.json` between invocations. Resume-mode units read carry fields before weight computation and write updated entries after each emission. Cold units never appear in the checkpoint units array.\r\n/app/environment/docs/persistence_notes.md:5:Partial lane requests must merge new resume entries with preserved checkpoints for resume units that were not requested in the current argv list.\r\n/app/environment/include/c9_api.h:6:const char *c9_resolve_mode(const char *manifest_mode, const char *unit_name, int pass_epoch);\r\n/app/environment/include/constants.h:5:constexpr std::uint64_t kDigestSeed = 1469598103934665603ull;\r\n/app/environment/include/constants.h:6:constexpr std::uint64_t kDigestStep = 1099511628211ull;\r\n/app/environment/include/lane_bridge.h:18:const char *forge_lane_mode(const char *manifest_mode, const char *unit_name, int pass_epoch);\r\n/app/environment/include/lane_bridge.h:21:                                   int pass_epoch, int64_t drift_total, "]
